---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy — Kick the Tires">

  <!-- Nav -->
  <nav class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-6 flex items-center justify-between">
    <a href="/" class="flex items-center gap-2">
      <span class="text-xl">🛞</span>
      <span class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 tracking-tight">Kick the Tires</span>
    </a>
    <a href="/" class="text-sm text-slate-500 hover:text-slate-800 transition-colors">
      ← Back
    </a>
  </nav>

  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-slate-400 mb-12">Last updated: April 2025</p>

    <div class="space-y-10 text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-3">What Kick the Tires does</h2>
        <p>
          Kick the Tires is a Chrome extension that displays car reliability information on AutoScout24 listing pages. It reads publicly visible listing data (such as make, model, fuel type, and mileage) on the page you are viewing to match it against our reliability database. All matching happens locally in your browser.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-3">Data we collect</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">We collect a small amount of anonymous usage data to improve the extension. This includes:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-slate-500">
          <li>Extension installed / uninstalled events</li>
          <li>Which car models are viewed (make, model, generation — never the listing URL or seller information)</li>
          <li>Whether reliability data was shown or the model was unsupported</li>
          <li>Interactions with the extension panel (opened, closed, tab switches)</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4">
          This data is sent to <a href="https://mixpanel.com" class="text-amber-600 hover:text-amber-700 underline underline-offset-2">Mixpanel</a>, our analytics provider. All events are anonymous — we do not collect your name, email, IP address, browsing history, or any information that could identify you personally.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-3">Data we do not collect</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-slate-500">
          <li>Personal information (name, email, address, phone number)</li>
          <li>Browsing history or activity outside of AutoScout24 pages</li>
          <li>Listing URLs, seller details, or pricing information</li>
          <li>Cookies or cross-site tracking data</li>
          <li>Login credentials or AutoScout24 account information</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-3">Permissions</h2>
        <p>
          The extension requires access to AutoScout24 pages only. It does not access any other websites or browser data. The specific permissions requested and their purposes are listed in the Chrome Web Store listing.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-3">Data storage and security</h2>
        <p>
          All reliability matching happens locally in your browser — no listing data is sent to our servers. Anonymous analytics events are transmitted to Mixpanel via encrypted HTTPS connections.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-3">Third parties</h2>
        <p>
          The only third-party service receiving data from the extension is Mixpanel (anonymous usage analytics). We do not sell, share, or transfer any data to other third parties.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-3">Your rights</h2>
        <p>
          Since we do not collect personal data, there is no personal data to access, correct, or delete. If you wish to stop all data collection, simply uninstall the extension.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-3">Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this privacy policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated date. Continued use of the extension after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-3">Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about this privacy policy? Reach us at
          <a href="mailto:info@kickthetires.ch" class="text-amber-600 hover:text-amber-700 underline underline-offset-2">info@kickthetires.ch</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </article>

  <!-- Footer -->
  <footer class="border-t border-slate-200 bg-slate-50">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-10 flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-4 text-sm text-slate-500">
      <p>© {new Date().getFullYear()} Kick the Tires · Built in Switzerland</p>
      <a href="mailto:info@kickthetires.ch" class="hover:text-slate-800 transition-colors">info@kickthetires.ch</a>
    </div>
  </footer>

</Layout>
